## Description
Enforces WCAG 2.1 minimum 44x44dp touch target size on all interactive elements.

## Problem
- Close buttons (X icons) are only ~24px, difficult to tap accurately
- Icon-only buttons don't meet touch target minimums
- Navigation links lack vertical padding for thumb tapping
- Gallery photo controls are too small for reliable interaction

## Solution
- Add `min-w-[44px] min-h-[44px]` to all icon buttons
- Update button size variants: sm→44px, icon→44px
- Add `flex items-center justify-center` to center icons
- Add `touch-manipulation` class to improve tap responsiveness
- Add minimum height to navigation links

## Impact
- 100% touch target compliance with WCAG 2.1 Level AA
- Fewer accidental taps and mis-taps
- Better thumb-zone ergonomics on large phones
- Improved accessibility for motor impairments

## Testing
- Verify all buttons ≥44x44dp using DevTools element inspector
- Test on iPhone SE (smallest screen) for thumb reachability
- Check spacing between adjacent targets (≥8px gap)
- Verify focus indicators visible at new sizes

## References
- WCAG 2.1 Success Criterion 2.5.5 (Level AAA: 44x44dp)
- Apple Human Interface Guidelines: 44pt minimum
- Material Design: 48dp minimum
